{
  "texts": [
    "(6.8)For a local correspondent of ♢ α □ β p → □ δ ♢ γ p, simply delete the ∀x from (6.8).For possibility frames, we have a very similar result in Proposition 6.23.",
    "Given a possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩ and sequence α = ⟨i 1,..., i n ⟩ of indices from I, define xR α y as above except that if α is the empty sequence, let xR α y iff y ⊑ x.",
    "Note that the R-down condition of standard frames implies:• if xR α y and y ′ ⊑ y, then xR α y ′.For the empty sequence, this means that if y ⊑ x and y ′ ⊑ y, then y ′ ⊑ x, which is just the transitivity of ⊑.We are now ready to prove the analogue of Proposition 6.22 in possibility semantics.Proposition 6.23 (Lemmon-Scott Possibility Frame Correspondence).",
    "Let F be a full standard possibility frame.",
    "Then for any sequences α, β, δ, and γ of indices from I, ♢ α □ β p → □ δ ♢ γ p is valid over F iff F satisfies ∀x∀y xR δ y → ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀z(x ′ R α z → ∃u(yR γ u ∧ zR β u))."
  ]
}